goals.question: What is the average yield of each variety across all sites and years?
goals.visualization: Bar chart of yield by variety
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the variety with the highest yield and the one with the lowest yield.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different sites?
goals.visualization: Box plot of yield by site
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the sites with the highest and lowest yield and the variability of yield across different sites.

goals.question: What is the trend of yield over the years?
goals.visualization: Line chart of yield by year
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is an increasing or decreasing trend of yield over the years.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify the range of yield values and the frequency of their occurrence.

goals.question: What is the relationship between yield and variety?
goals.visualization: Scatter plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: This visualization will help us identify if there is a correlation between yield and variety, and if certain varieties perform better than others.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['yield'])
    data = data.groupby(['variety'])['yield'].mean().reset_index()
    data = data.sort_values(by=['yield'], ascending=False)
    plt.bar(data['variety'], data['yield'])
    plt.title('What is the average yield of each variety across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylabel('Yield')
    plt.xlabel('Variety')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.boxplot(data.groupby('site')['yield'].apply(list), labels=data['site'].unique())
    ax.set_xlabel('Site')
    ax.set_ylabel('Yield')
    ax.set_title('How does the yield vary across different sites?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='coerce')
    data = data.sort_values(by='year')
    plt.plot(data['year'], data['yield'])
    plt.title('What is the trend of yield over the years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    plt.hist(data['yield'], bins=20, color='green', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['yield'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['yield'].median(), color='blue', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['yield'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
